org.middleheaven.sequence
Interface Sequence<T>

All Known Subinterfaces:
IdentitySequence<I>, LimitedSequence<T>, NamedSequence<T>, RandomSequence<T>, StateEditableSequence<T>, StatePersistentSequence<T>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractStatePersistanteSequence, IntegerIdentitySequence, IterableBasedSequence, LongSequence, NamedSequenceAdapter, RandomCharSequence, RandomNumberSequence, SequenceAdapter, UUIDIdentitySequence
public interface Sequence<T>

Interface for all sequences. Sequences generate the next token in a series. Sequences are unlimited. Limited sequences must implement LimitedSequence that acts like a iterator.

Author:
Sergio M. M. Taborda
